# Radio Ad-Sensing Pipeline — Agent Conventions

## Canonical docs (read first)

0. `AGENTS.md` — **session memory**: current phase, state, checklist (read every session)
1. `PLAN.md` — architecture, schema, phases, risks (do not re-litigate)
2. `plan/handoff-*.md` — phase scope for current work
3. `plan/phase1-report.md` — Phase 1 completion record

## Code layout

- `shared/` — import-light; DB, models, config, logging (no GPU/ML deps)
- `config/stations.yaml`, `config/settings.yaml` — runtime config
- `data/` — gitignored runtime (DB, chunks, archives)
- Service stubs: `ingestor/`, `worker/`, `alerter/`, `dashboard/`, `monitoring/`

## Hard constraints

- SQLite: WAL + `shared/db.py` `retry_on_busy`; keep transactions short
- `fingerprints.chromaprint_vector` = BLOB feature vector, not hash
- LLM schema: no `station`/`timestamp` in extraction — metadata only
- Telegram: outbound-only; secrets in `.env` never committed
- Implement **one phase at a time** per handoff scope

## Verification before "done"

Agent **runs these automatically** — see `.cursor/rules/agent-commands.mdc` §2 (never ask user to type):

```powershell
cd h:\DEV\projects\radio-ad-sensing-pipeline
.venv\Scripts\pytest -q
.venv\Scripts\python -c "from shared.db import migrate; migrate('data/test.db')"
```

Report deviations in `plan/` when closing a phase.
